The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Frontpage | Ulfa camp busted 
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Ulfa camp busted 
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                               
	Shillong, May 7: Meghalaya police today busted an Ulfa transit camp at Bilbot in Malangkona village in the West Khasi Hills bordering Assam and seized six US hand grenades and demand notes after an encounter with the militants. The police said after getting information on the presence of Ulfa militants in the area, Meghalaya police approached the makeshift camp today at 5pm. The militants in the camp opened fire, forcing the police to fire back. The militants later fled.                                                                                                                                           
